This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with reinforcement learning and model-based approaches. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves decision-making and planning. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) as it deals with modeling the environment and selecting actions. It could also be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it involves control and optimization. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it involves estimating values and selecting models.
